        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4088622880" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3208034030705149661">If you know me and my reading tastes, you know that I am always on the look out for books based in Paris. Imagine my luck when I found this book, written by &quot;the most-read French author alive today&quot;<br/><br/>The book is romantic, funny, and touching. I really really enjoyed it but in parts. Mia is a British actress playing a woman in love with her real-life husband. But she&apos;s fed up of her cheating husband and to lay low while the movie releases, she escapes to Paris to live with her best friend. There sh</span>
  <span id="freeText3208034030705149661" style="display:none">If you know me and my reading tastes, you know that I am always on the look out for books based in Paris. Imagine my luck when I found this book, written by "the most-read French author alive today"<br /><br />The book is romantic, funny, and touching. I really really enjoyed it but in parts. Mia is a British actress playing a woman in love with her real-life husband. But she's fed up of her cheating husband and to lay low while the movie releases, she escapes to Paris to live with her best friend. There she meets Paul, an American author who is still trying to catch up to the fame and adoration he received with his debut book. And as luck would have it, his best friend sets up a date with Mia through a dating website - In the city of LOVE.<br /><br />This book did have a lot of potential. I loved the setting and the complications that these characters were coming from. But the writing style made it really difficult for me to enjoy the book, maybe because it's a translation. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3208034030705149661" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


